{"_id":"0h5xOAtzV4mm7X7D","name":"Wretched Royalty","permission":{"default":0,"xVCY8TaEyq1Er5RJ":3},"type":"class","data":{"abilities":"<p>Painfully average, you adjust no abilities. Roll a d8 on the weapons table. Roll a d4 on the armor table but reroll if you receive heavy armor. You begin with two of the following:</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<ol>\n<li>The Blade of you Ancestors</li>\n<li>&lsquo;Poltroon&rsquo; the Court Jester</li>\n<li>Barbarister the Incredible Horse</li>\n<li>Hamfund the Squire</li>\n<li>The Snake-Skin Gift</li>\n<li>Horn of the Schleswig Lords!</li>\n</ol>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Things were going so well, until&hellip; (d6)</p>\n<ol>\n<li>your W&auml;stland palace was reduced to rubble.</li>\n<li>your caravan kingdom of Tveland fell into penury.</li>\n<li>King Fathmu IX's brother Zigmund, your father, was murdered.</li>\n<li>the southern empire of S&uuml;dglans sank into the sea.</li>\n<li>Anthelia demanded a gift of royal blood</li>\n<li>two young princes were kidnapped west of Bergen Chrypt and disappeared into the black crevasse of the eastern slopes.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","armorTableDie":"1d3","description":"Bowed down only by the memories of your own lost glory, you could never submit to anyone else. Not you, of noble blood! (Not that you expect any of these peons to understand the depths of your sorrow.)","omenDie":"1d2","startingAgility":"3d6","startingHitPoints":"1d6","startingItems":"morkborg.class-wretched-royalty,Painfully Average","startingPresence":"3d6","startingRolls":"morkborg.rolls-wretched-royalty,Wretched Royalty Items,2\nmorkborg.rolls-wretched-royalty,Things were going so well until,1","startingSilver":"4d6*10","startingStrength":"3d6","startingToughness":"3d6","weaponTableDie":"1d8"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/tokens/players/wretched_royalty.png","effects":[]}
